  "system": {
    "biography": "<p>A man-eating water-horse of Scottish legend: it lures riders, then its highly adhesive skin traps them as it drags them under to drown and devour.</p><p><strong>Powers:</strong> Compulsion (LOS), Engulf, Enhanced Movement, Enhanced Senses (Low-Light Vision, Sonar)</p><p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong> Dietary Requirements (Human/Metahuman Flesh)</p><p><em>Attacks: 6S, Reach −1. Habitat: Freshwater rivers, lochs, lakes, estuaries and fjords (seawater-tolerant). Range: Rare throughout northern Europe, especially Scotland and Tir Nan Og. Anyone touching it makes a Strength Test (TN = its Essence) to free the affected body part or weapon. Swimming Quickness multiplier 5. 3D6 Initiative dice. Book Body 10/1 (Hardened Armor 1), Intelligence 2/4. PAE p.39.</em></p>",
